<h3 id="Input">Input helper</h3>

<p>        
    In order to render text inputs you will need to use the 
    <code>@@Html.BsInputFor</code> helper extension and 
    decorate your model property with <code>BsControlAttribute</code> and <code>DisplayAttribute</code>.
    You can choose from standard HTML inputs like
    <code>Text</code>, <code>Password</code>, <code>TextArea</code>
    or HTML5 flavored inputs like
    <code>Email</code>, <code>Url</code>, <code>Number</code>, <code>Color</code>.
</p>

<p>
    All the text inputs rendered by <code>@@Html.BsInputFor</code> supports placeholder and description tooltip, 
    the placeholder text is extracted from the <code>Prompt</code> property of the <code>Display</code> attribute 
    while the description tooltip is using the <code>Description</code> propery.
</p>

<p>        
    Besides text inputs, <code>BsInputFor</code> helper can render the following types: 
    <code>Checkbox</code>, <code>Radio</code>, <code>Date</code>, <code>Time</code>, <code>Datetime</code> and <code>File</code>.
</p>

